                        "content": "A client has been started on zolpidem. After instructing the client in how to obtain the maximal effect of zolpidem, the nurse determines that the client demonstrates understanding of correct administration of the medication by which statement?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nZolpidem is a hypnotic. The client would be instructed to take the medication at bedtime and to swallow the medication whole with a full glass of water. For faster onset of sleep, the client needs to be instructed not to take the medication with food or immediately after a meal. Antacids affect the absorption of the medication.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Evaluate Outcomes\nCognitive Ability: Evaluating\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Barbiturate and Sedative-Hypnotics\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Anxiety Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Evaluation\nPriority Concepts: Safety, Patient Education\nStrategies: Comparable or Alike Options, Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the subject, obtaining maximal effect of the medication. Also, note that options 1, 2, and 4 are comparable or alike in that they indicate taking the medication with food.\n ",
                        "id": "2798f9c67c304e1ea48359c15b5e6686",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
