                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nDiazepam is a sedative hypnotic that also has anticonvulsant and skeletal muscle relaxant properties. The nurse would institute safety measures before leaving the client's room to prevent injury as a result of medication side effects, which include dizziness, drowsiness, and lethargy. The other options listed are useful but not essential to the client's safety in this situation.\n\nClient Needs: Safe and Effective Care Environment\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Prioritize Hypotheses\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Barbiturate and Sedative-Hypnotics\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Safety\nStrategies: Maslow's Hierarchy of Needs Theory, Strategic Words, Umbrella Option\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, most important. First, recall the action and effects of this medication. Next, use Maslow's Hierarchy of Needs theory to prioritize. If a physiological need is not addressed, safety is the priority. Additionally, the correct option is the umbrella option.\n ",
